cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC

The paper deals with the translation of algorithmic descriptions of discrete functions to SAT for the purpose of cryptanalysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and software systems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses theoretical principles, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
